Show HN: List of Companies That Use Next.js and Tailwind CSS
text:
I love the stack and am curating a list for myself in case I ever want to apply for jobs.

Companies using Tailwind in particular attract me because they tend to have the same build fast mindset I have so its also an indirect filter for culture. What do you think?

Also - If you can think of any cool companies using Next/Tailwind/Both please do comment/PR. :)

Note: I am trying to only add companies that are early stage/ startups and use it for their main product (one off web pages don't count)

Need advice on making an idea known
text:
I'm no scientist or engineer. I dropped out of engineering in the first year, so I have a very basic knowledge of physics.

I have an idea (a rather simple one if I need to explain it) that could help solve droughts in some regions, and could also be used to store excess energy from solar PV panels or other forms of non-constant electrical energy production. It's not really "new" in the sense of that there is no new specialized technical process (or there might be in some parts, but I don't think I could design the technical details - though I thnk it would be based on existing processes).

How can I spread this idea in a way that many people know it and attach it to my name, or at least don't associate it to some random rich guy? How could I spread it in a way that NO ONE can patent it, take advantage of it by preventing others from using it or charging a lot of money for something that should be used for the good of many? Do I need to make a proof of concept to convince people?

Are there science/engineering forums that have lots of users where stuff like this can be discussed?
